Description: Reddish glazed composition amulet in the form of a wedjat-eye with a pierced suspension ring at the top.
Curator's comments: Provenance not specified in the Museum register, but possibly from Tell Dafana, according to the context of the item in the list, if not from Tell Nabasha or any other Eastern Delta site excavated by Petrie in 1886.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.45, p.60, p.180, pl.22)
